James de Villiers, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Crammond &ndash; Two alleged hijackers were injured when a vehicle they allegedly stole rolled of the R33 in Crammond, KwaZulu-Natal, on Friday evening, paramedics said.&nbsp;A third man was apparently travelling with the men but was not found on the scene, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement on Saturday.&nbsp;When paramedics arrived on the scene, one patient was found in a critical condition and one sustained minor injuries.Both were lying outside the vehicle on the side of the road.&nbsp;The patients were treated and the critically injured provided with advanced life support interventions.&nbsp;Once treated, the patients were transported to Greys and Northdale Hospital for further treatment.&nbsp;Authorities were deployed to the scene for further investigation.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.